summary: This document provides detailed information on how to view aircraft records, including the types of files contained on a CD Rom, the format of the records, and the sequence in which documents are displayed. It outlines the various document types related to aircraft records and their contents, emphasizing the organization and retrieval of these records.
keyFacts: The document describes the structure and content of aircraft records available on CD Rom.
It explains the different types of files included, such as Airworthiness, Registration, and Suspense files.
The document outlines how records are organized by acceptance or recording date.
It mentions the use of bookmarks in Acrobat Reader for navigating the aircraft records.
There are references to protective orders affecting certain paragraphs of the document.
